  "body": "By default Truffle shows events emitted by a contract when a test fails. However in v2.0.7 , it doesn't. \nYou can reproduce by using the truffle sample generated using `truffle init` and modify the MetaCoin contract for example adding a simple event to the `sendCoin` function. Then making the test using it fail by changing the assertion for example to `assert.equal(balance.valueOf(), 1000, \"10000 wasn't in the first account\");`\n\n```\nevent MyEvent(uint now);\n\nfunction sendCoin(address receiver, uint amount) returns(bool sufficient) {\n     if (balances[msg.sender] < amount) return false;\n    balances[msg.sender] -= amount;\n    balances[receiver] += amount;\n    return true;\n}\n```\n\nThis issue makes troubleshooting contract code really tough.\n",
